OL,3,CReeves faces up to the mother of all
OL,4,Cfiscal crises
OL,6,FHere, in crude terms, is the nightmare
OL,7,Ffaced by the chancellor and the prime
OL,8,Fminister in the final two weeks before
OL,9,Fthe budget - which explains why senior
OL,10,Fministers led by the Deputy Prime
OL,11,FMinister Angela Rayner are complaining
OL,12,Fthey are being asked to make
OL,13,Funreasonable cuts.
OL,15,FThe sum that Chancellor Rachel Reeves
OL,16,Fneeds to find, to provide an adequate
OL,17,Fincrease in resources for the cash
OL,18,Fhungry NHS while providing real
OL,19,Fincreases to other departments, is in
OL,20,Fthe range of #35 billion to #50
OL,21,Fbillion.
