OL,3,CReeves faces up to the mother of all
OL,4,Cfiscal crises
OL,6,FThis is an almost unprecedented sum
OL,7,Ffor any chancellor to find.
OL,9,FThe two big tax increases which the
OL,10,FTreasury is working on - making
OL,11,Femployers' pension contributions
OL,12,Fsubject to national insurance and
OL,13,Fincreasing the basic rate of capital
OL,14,Fgains tax to between 30% and 35% -
OL,15,Fcould reasonably be expected to raise
OL,16,Fa bit over #20 billion.
