OL,3,CReeves faces up to the mother of all
OL,4,Cfiscal crises
OL,6,FThe point is that any other
OL,7,Fsubstantial tax increases would breach
OL,8,FKeir Starmer's and Labour's manifesto
OL,9,Fpromises, which I am assured Reeves
OL,10,Fwill not do.
OL,12,FThere is probably some scope to borrow
OL,13,Fa bit more for day-to-day spending, as
OL,14,Fa result of the roll-over of the fifth
OL,15,Fyear in the OBR's fiscal forecast. But
OL,16,Fthat won't release more than another
OL,17,F#10 billion or so.
